GTTimeStampImplicit_st Struct Reference
[Verification]

This structure represents the implicit data computed from a timestamp.

#include <gt_base.h>

Field Documentation

GT_UInt64 GTTimeStampImplicit_st::location_id

Timestamp issuer address within the GuardTime network. Extracted from the shape of the location hash chain. Internally, the address is a concatenation of four 16-bit fields and it would be reasonable to divide it up accordingly for displaying to the users.

char* GTTimeStampImplicit_st::public_key_fingerprint

Public key fingerprint, in base 32. Present only if GT_PUBLIC_KEY_SIGNATURE_PRESENT is set in GTVerificationInfo::verification_status.

char* GTTimeStampImplicit_st::publication_string

Control string for verifying the timestamp using a hardcopy publication, the value is base32(time+alg+hash+crc32).

GT_Time_t64 GTTimeStampImplicit_st::registered_time

The time when the GuardTime core registered the timestamp. Extracted from the shape of the history hash chain.
